  "narrative": "<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Short impact summary</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Despite the absence of citation and community discourse metrics, \"Mongameli Mabona,\" published by Leuven University Press in 2021, demonstrates commercial potential and relevance to sustainability through global frameworks.</p>\n<h3 class=\"story-subheading\">Full narrative</h3>\n<p class=\"story-text\">Published in 2021 by Leuven University Press, \"Mongameli Mabona\" serves as a notable scholarly work especially within the commercial landscape. With a strong commercial linkage evidenced by its presence on major platforms such as Amazon and Goodreads, this work indicates a recognized market interest that transcends traditional academic audiences.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">While the publication does not showcase substantial online mentions or community discourse, its relevance is supported by a modest engagement with sustainability concepts. The work is affiliated with at least one Sustainable Development Goal (SDG), suggesting that it contributes to broader discussions on sustainability and policy. This connection highlights its potential impact on scholarly and policy-oriented discussions related to global challenges.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">The lack of citations currently recorded may suggest that the work is in an early stage of uptake within the academic community. However, the information available indicates a growing opportunity for future engagement, whether through increasing citations or expanding its reach within more diverse platforms. This aligns with the common trajectory of new scholarly outputs becoming influential over time.</p>\n<p class=\"story-text\">In summary, while \"Mongameli Mabona\" may not yet have garnered significant academic attention, its commercial viability and association with sustainability suggest that it holds promise for engaging with both scholarly and broader societal topics in the future.</p>",
